<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> have a word with someone • have words with someone</xh5><p> <i>have a word with someone—</i>have a short conversation with a person: The personnel manager said he wanted to <u>have a word with</u> me.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression is not equivalent in meaning to the phrase <b>have a word in someone’s ear</b>—<i>give a brief message to a person in confidence:</i> My employer, the cadi, wants to <u>have a word in your ear</u>.</p><p> <i>have words with someone—</i>have a quarrel with smb.: Our cab arrived and the same man whom we <u>had words with</u> a few minutes earlier came out.</p> </entry>
